# API Conventions

## Endpoints

- All REST endpoints live under `/api/v1/`
- Controllers return `ResponseEntity<T>` or `Mono<ResponseEntity<T>>`
- Never expose entity classes directly in API responses — always use DTOs
- Pagination: `page` (0-based), `size`, `sortBy` (whitelisted), `order` (ASC/DESC)
- Use `@Operation(summary = "...")` from SpringDoc on every endpoint

## Security

- If `orinuno.security.api-key` is configured, `ApiKeyAuthFilter` checks `X-API-KEY` header
- Health endpoints (`/api/v1/health/*`) are always open
- Swagger/actuator endpoints are not protected by API key

## SQL Injection Prevention

- `sortBy` and `order` parameters MUST be validated against a whitelist before passing to MyBatis
- Never use `${...}` interpolation in MyBatis XML without prior validation
- Use `#{...}` (parameterized) for all user-supplied values
